This paper investigates two black-hat online marketplaces and their services, sellers, and customers. The paper focuses on the measurement-based analysis of these marketplaces, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also analyzes the social and economic aspects of these marketplaces, which could be categorized under social networks (cs.SI), cybercrime (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SOC), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
